  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Biventricular Pacing has been shown an improvement of symptoms in patients with heart
      failure.

      A temporary pacing is necessary in patients after cardiac procedures. In patients with
      hypertrophic cardiomyopathy, a single right ventricular pacing can decrease the cardiac
      output and blood pressure.

      The investigators propose that biventricular pacing in these patients and conditions results
      in an improvement of symptoms instead of single right pacing.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
